item.title: How do i change the name and ending place of teleports?
item.dc:creator: @Maxie35 Maxie35
item.description:
@Maxie35 wrote:

Well to start off, for the “home” button to go to varrock go into your client.java and search for the ::home command.

That should look like this:

else if (command.equalsIgnoreCase("home")) { if (teleblock == true) { sendMessage("A magical force stops you from teleporting."); } else { teleportToX = 2827; teleportToY = 9808; sendMessage("You teleport to Home.");

Change the X and Y coords to the coords you want to teleport to, to get the coords type ::coords or in some server it shows the coords at the emote tab if i’m right… and because in your client.java that button (probably case 168 i think for home) will teleport you to home because it works with the command: home

And i forgot how to change the spell text, i can do it for ancient spells but cant find normal spells, ill tell you when i found it
